  "Any WebDAV-compatible service works with this plugin:\n\n- Nextcloud (recommended)\n- ownCloud\n- Synology NAS\n- QNAP NAS\n- Box.com (with WebDAV)\n- Apache mod_dav\n- nginx with WebDAV module\n\nNote: Some services require app-specific passwords for WebDAV access.": "",
  "Authentication is required for API v2 if you've enabled it in OpenLP's Remote plugin settings. The plugin uses HTTP Basic Authentication. Most local network setups don't require authentication, but it's recommended for security.": "",
  "Before relying on external backups, test your connection:\n1. Go to Plugins > External Backup\n2. Click 'Test WebDAV Connection'\n3. Verify you see a success message\n\nCommon issues:\n- 401/403 errors: Check username and password\n- Connection timeout: Verify the endpoint URL is correct\n- Certificate errors: Ensure the WebDAV server has a valid SSL certificate": "",
  "Choose what appears when no Gravatar exists:\n• Mystery Person - Gray silhouette outline\n• Identicon - Geometric pattern based on email\n• MonsterID - Unique generated monster face\n• Wavatar - Abstract generated face\n• Retro - 8-bit arcade-style pixel art\n• RoboHash - Unique generated robot\n• Blank - Transparent (falls back to initials)": "",
